revision.text:
== Mikawa Seven Lucky Gods ==
'''Mikawa Seven Lucky Gods''' (三河七福神, Mikawa Shichifukujin) is a pilgrimage route consisting of seven {{ill|temples|ja|寺院}} in the {{ill|Mikawa Province|ja|三河国}} region of {{ill|Aichi Prefecture|ja|愛知県}}, dedicated to the {{ill|Seven Lucky Gods|ja|七福神}}.

== Overview ==
* Founded: {{ill|1979|ja|1979年}}
* Area: {{ill|Okazaki|ja|岡崎市}}, {{ill|Hekinan|ja|碧南市}}, {{ill|Gamagōri|ja|蒲郡市}}, {{ill|Toyokawa|ja|豊川市}}, {{ill|Nishio|ja|西尾市}}
* Open: Year-round

== List of Mikawa Seven Lucky Gods ==
* {{ill|Hōzō-ji (Okazaki)|ja|法蔵寺 (岡崎市)}} (Okazaki) - {{ill|Ebisu|ja|恵比須}}
* {{ill|Anraku-ji (Gamagōri)|ja|安楽寺 (蒲郡市)}} (Gamagōri) - {{ill|Daikokuten|ja|大黒天}}
* {{ill|Hōfuku-ji (Okazaki)|ja|宝福寺 (岡崎市)}} (Okazaki) - {{ill|Fukurokuju|ja|福禄寿}}
* {{ill|Sanmyō-ji|ja|三明寺}} (Toyokawa) - {{ill|Benzaiten|ja|弁才天}}
* {{ill|Myōfuku-ji (Hekinan)|ja|妙福寺 (碧南市)}} (Hekinan) - {{ill|Bishamonten|ja|毘沙門天}}
* {{ill|Chōen-ji (Nishio)|ja|長圓寺 (西尾市)}} (Nishio) - {{ill|Hotei|ja|布袋}}
* {{ill|Hōju-in (Nishio)|ja|宝珠院 (西尾市)}} (Nishio) - {{ill|Jurōjin|ja|寿老人}}

== Related Topics ==
* {{ill|Yoshida Seven Lucky Gods|ja|吉田七福神}}

== External Links ==
* [http://www.aruku88.net/7fuku/04mikawa/index.html Reference Site] {{ill|Broken link|ja|リンク切れ}} (as of November 2016)

{{ill|Japan culture stub|ja|Japan-culture-stub}}

{{ill|Citation needed|ja|みかわしちふくしん}}

